\title{HaplotypeRainbow}
\description{
An R6 class for building haplotype "rainbow" plots. The class carries the mapping
of your four data columns (sample, target, haplotype identifier and relative counts)
so it only has to be supplied once. Methods that transform state (\code{prep()},
\code{sort_by_clustering()}, \code{set_sample_order()}, \code{sort_alphabetical()}) mutate the object
and return it invisibly, so they can be chained; \code{plot()} returns a \link[ggplot2:ggplot]{ggplot2::ggplot}
object.

Column defaults follow the Portable Microhaplotype Object (PMO) convention:
\code{library_sample_name}, \code{target_name}, \code{seq} and \code{reads}.
}
